comments.body:
@danishprakash Ya, I gave up on the PPA and OBS repos long ago. Their maintenance turned out to be unsustainable.

@SuhasSrinivasan I guess ubuntu and debian sometimes provide a `backports` repo for LTS which might get you a newer build. If not, quite sometime ago, I was told Debian's `experimental` repo often works on ubuntu, so maybe worth a try. If neither of those work, I'd suggest filing a request with the Ubuntu's official tracker.

Another alternative would be to use [podman's official container image](https://quay.io/repository/podman/stable) . 

Hope that helps.

Closing..
